article.headline: Tulsa 74, Rice 68
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Anthony Price had 16 points and 11 rebounds as Tulsa handed Rice its first Western Athletic Conference loss, 74-68 Saturday. Price and his teammates held Michael Harris to 10 points, well behind his 19.1 average. The Owls (11-4, 3-1 WAC) fell behind 26-4 and 31-8 early in the game but battled back to close within 49-45 with 10:55 to play and to 54-51 at 6:21 on two free throws by Brock Gillespie. Tulsa (6-8, 2-3 WAC) got two free throws from Jarius Glenn and a 3-pointer from Seneca Collins to restore a 59-51 lead, then made enough plays down the stretch to keep the Owls at bay. Jason Parker led Tulsa with 22 points, 15 of those in the first 12 minutes. Glenn had 20 points and five rebounds, while Guilherme Teichmann added eight points and 11 rebounds. Jason McKrieth led Rice with 19 points and added 10 rebounds, while J.R. Harrison had 13 points and 12 rebounds. The Owls had seasons lows for points (22) and shooting percentage (25) in falling behind 35-22 at the half. Tulsa, which leads the WAC in field goal percentage defense, held the Owls to 34 percent for the game (22-64). Price, who also had four steals and four blocks, made consecutive baskets, including a slam off a lob pass from Seneca Collins, to give Tulsa a 67-58 cushion with 1:45 to play. Tulsa was up 72-60 after two free throws by Teichmann with 44 seconds left. Rice scored the games final six points.
